@node "INTRO" "iNTRODUCTiON"

                                  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 This is the free version of dCN!NUKE 1.0 by Derrow (dCN-/F·dEZiGN)! dCN!NUKE is
 a  FIM-Door for the use with the FAME BBS System. This tool enables you to award
 and deduct credits for uploads, make them free download and much more.

 dCN!NUKE contains the special 'dERROW sEARCH aLGORYTHM rOUTINE' which is one of
 the  fastest  algorythms  to  search  for  the  up/downloader(s) of a file. It's
 incredible fast, and very save to use ! This implies that dCN!Nuke finds ALLWAYS
 the  correct  uploader, even on dupe-uploads. No more fucking around because the
 credits where taken from the wrong User. This is now past...
  
 dCN!Nuke is so multi-configurable, that it is really a pleasure to use it.

 So, install it and enjoy...!

 The @{"cONFIGURATION" link "E4" 0}  is  done  by  the  Preferences-Editor.  See
 @{"iNSTALLATION" link "E3" 0} for more information.
@endnode

@node "REQUIRE" "rEQUIREMENTS"

                        @{b}@{u}Requirements for dCN!Nuke v1.0 usage@{ub}@{uu}

 - An Amiga with operating system V2.04+

 - FAME Mailbox Mainpart v1.14+ 
   FAME Mailbox System Editor v1.6+ 
   FAME Mailbox Server v1.6+
   FAME.library 4.1+

@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "iNSTALLATION"

                                  @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

 To install this fine piece of work just use  the  Installer-script  coming with
 this archive.

 If  you  have  a  MC68020  or  higher  the  Installer  will check and choose the
 optimized version for you.
@endnode

@node "QUICK" "   qUICK  gUIDE   "

                         @{b}@{u}Quick Installation Guide@{ub}@{uu}


To setup this tool the fastest way simply follow this steps:

 - 1.   Execute the Installation program provided with this archive.

 - 2.
     2.1  Start FAME:Doors/dCN!NUKE/dCN!NUKEPrefs from WB.
     2.2  Now add your Name/Handle to "Access/Secure", or select "Nuker All".
     2.3  SAVE the settings end exit the Prefs Editor.

 - 3.   Start NUKE from the mainprompt of FAME and enjoy!
@endnode

