@node "PatchTopData.FIM" "PatchTopData.FIM"

                                 @{b}@{u}PatchTopData.FIM@{ub}@{uu}

 @{fg shine}Discription@{fg fill}..:@{fg text}
               This external Programm, is needed, to update the Data-Files of
               dCN!Top v2.0 when nuking some Files from a User!

 @{fg shine}Placement@{fg fill}....:@{fg text}
               Put this File in: @{fg shine}'FAME:Doors/dCN!Nuke/PatchTopData.FIM'@{fg text}

 @{fg shine}BBS/SYSCMD@{fg fill}...:@{fg text}
               Install this Door as BBSCMD with the name 'PatchTD'.

 @{fg shine}How it works@{fg fill}.:@{fg text}
               When you nuke an Uploaded File from a User, then dCN!Nuke checks
               if the file was uploaded this week or not!

               If it was uploaded this week, then dCN!Nuke launches
               'PatchTopData.FIM', which then will decrease the Upload Bytes of
               the User, with the amount of the 'REAL' Filesize of that file!

               This means, if you nuke the File (in ex. 2 times),
               PatchTopData.FIM will only decrease the Uploadbytes of
               the dCN!Top-Data, for '1 time'!

               The updates to the dCN!Top-DataFiles,of course will be made to 
               dCN!Conftop.data, and to dCN!Weektop.data. 
 
 @{i}Now you will ALLWAY's have the 'REAL' upload Bytes of a User, in the@{ui} 
 @{i}Conftop/Weektop Bulletins.@{ui}
@endnode

@node "CONFIG" "cONFIGURATION"

                                 @{b}@{u}Configuration@{ub}@{uu}

                      @{u}Preferences-Editor for dCN!NUKE V1.0@{uu}

 The configuration of dCN!NUKE is completely  done  by  this  Prefs-program. The
 editor is used to set the default settings and some other options for dCN!NUKE.

                           @{u}dCN!NUKE PREFERENCES v1.0@{uu}

                      @{"  Default Prefs  " link "CFGDEF" 0} @{"  Access/Secure  " link "CFGACC" 0}
                      @{"  Size Comments  " link "CFGSIZ" 0} @{"  Color Config   " link "CFGCOL" 0}
                      @{"  File Comments  " link "CFGFIL" 0} @{"  ConfSpy Config " link "CFGCSC" 0}
                      @{"  Byte Comments  " link "CFGBYT" 0} @{"  NukeLog Config " link "CFGNKL" 0}

                      @{"      ABOUT      " link "CFGABO" 0} @{"      EXIT       " link "CFGEXI" 0}
@endnode

@node "CFGDEF" "Default Preferences"

                          @{b}@{u}Default Settings@{ub}@{uu}


 @{fg shine}Nuker Launch All@{fg fill}.......:@{fg text}
                         If activated: Every User is able to launch dCN!Nuke.
                         The settings in 'Access/Secure' will be overridden.

 @{fg shine}Wildcard Support@{fg fill}.......:@{fg text}
                         Enables the usage of AmigaDOS wildcards for the
                         Filename-entry (#?,*).

 @{fg shine}Extern Comment@{fg fill}.........:@{fg text}
                         Enables the user to write an additional comment to
                         the receiver's Nuke-message.

 @{fg shine}Create Fakefiles@{fg fill}.......:@{fg text}
                         If a file can't be found, btw. it doesn't exist, the
                         User will be prompted if he want's to create a fakefile.
                         If so, a small file will be created with the corresponding
                         filename in order to continue with the nuking Process.

 @{fg shine}Delete File physikaly@{fg fill}..:@{fg text}
                         If activated: The corresponding file will really be nuked,
                         ie. the file will be overwritten with the
                         comment: "Nuked with dCN!Nuke".
                         
                         If deactivated, the files won't be overwritten. Just
                         their protection bits will be cleared, so they are no
                         longer readable, and nobody is able download these files.
                         The files itself stay completely intact.

 @{fg shine}Logfile Active?@{fg fill}........:@{fg text}
                         If activated: Every usage of dCN!Nuke will be logged in
                         a Logfile, named as defined below in 'Logfile'.

 @{fg shine}Logfile@{fg fill}................:@{fg text}
                         The path and name of the Logfile to log the Nuker-actions.
                         Default: "Doors:dCN!Nuke/dCN!Nuke.log".

 @{fg shine}FreeDL Text@{fg fill}............:@{fg text}
                         This string will be used as a comment for those Freedownload
                         files.

@endnode

@node "CFGSIZ" "Size Comments"

                          @{b}@{u}Size Comments@{ub}@{uu}

@{i}Here you can enter the comments which replace the bytesize of a  nuked  file in the
filelisting. On the left you see a list with your  old  entries.  All changes  you  do
will immediately show up in this list. If you want to edit one listentry just select it
and  modify  it  in  the  input line.@{ui}

@{fg shine}NEW ENTRY@{fg fill}..............:@{fg text}
                         With this you add a new entry to the list. Now you can enter
                         a comment of max. 7 chars in the line below the list.
                         The entry will be added to the list on pressing @{i}RETURN@{ui}.

@{fg shine}COPY ENTRY@{fg fill}.............:@{fg text}
                         This button copies the selected entry into the list. An
                         identically entry will also be added to the bottom of the
list,
                         where you can edit it.

@{fg shine}DELETE ENTRY@{fg fill}...........:@{fg text}
                         By clicking here you can delete an entry from the list.
@endnode

@node "CFGFIL" "File Comments"

                          @{b}@{u}File Comments@{ub}@{uu}

@{i}This function defines comments, which will be added below the description of a file. On
the left you see a list with your  old  entries.  All  changes  you  do will
immediately show up in this list. If you want to edit one listentry just select it and
modify  it  in  the  input line.@{ui}

@{fg shine}NEW ENTRY@{fg fill}..............:@{fg text}
                         With this you add a new entry to the list. Now you can enter
                         a comment of max. 7 chars in the line below the list.
                         The entry will be added to the list on pressing @{i}RETURN@{ui}.

@{fg shine}COPY ENTRY@{fg fill}.............:@{fg text}
                         This button copies the selected entry into the list. An
                         identically entry will also be added to the bottom of the
list,
                         where you can edit it.

@{fg shine}DELETE ENTRY@{fg fill}...........:@{fg text}
                         By clicking here you can delete an entry from the list.
@endnode

@node "CFGBYT" "Byte Comments"

                          @{b}@{u}Byte Comments@{ub}@{uu}

@{i}This function defines the comment which is below the description of a file. This is
where the user`s name and/or an action (what has been done with his file) stands. There
are the following variables:

@{fg fill} %N @{fg text} insert the user`s name.
@{fg fill} %c @{fg text} the factor of the current action will be inserted.

@{i}
On the left you see a list with your  old  entries.  All  changes  you  do  will
immediately show up in this list. If you want to edit one listentry just select it and
modify  it  in  the  input line. If you use variables you should try to keep the
comments as short as possible.@{ui}

@{fg shine}NEW ENTRY@{fg fill}..............:@{fg text}
                         With this you add a new entry to the list. Now you can enter
                         a comment of max. 7 chars in the line below the list.
                         The entry will be added to the list on pressing @{i}RETURN@{ui}.

@{fg shine}COPY ENTRY@{fg fill}.............:@{fg text}
                         This button copies the selected entry into the list. An
                         identically entry will also be added to the bottom of the
list,
                         where you can edit it.

@{fg shine}DELETE ENTRY@{fg fill}...........:@{fg text}
                         By clicking here you can delete an entry from the list.
@endnode

@node "CFGACC" "Access/Security"

                          @{b}@{u}Acess/Security@{ub}@{uu}

@{i}Here are the users listed who are allowed to use  the  nuker.  There  is  no
possibility to give access via a special accesslevel, as this has caused lots of damage
in the past. On the left you see a list with your  old  entries.  All changes  you  do
will immediately show up in this list. If you want to edit one listentry just select it
and  modify  it  in  the  input line.@{ui}

@{fg shine}Password@{fg fill}..............:@{fg text}
                         Here you can enter the password of the currently selected
                         user. It will be asked from him if he tries to nuke.

@{fg shine}NEW@{fg fill}...................:@{fg text}
                         This button copies the selected entry into the list. An
                         identically entry will also be added to the bottom of the
list,
                         where you can edit it.

@{fg shine}DELETE@{fg fill}................:@{fg text}
                         By clicking here you can delete an entry from the list.
@endnode

@node "CFGCOL" "Colour Config"

                           @{b}@{u}Colour Config@{ub}@{uu}

Here you can select a colour for every comment. The format is  the  same  as  in normal
ansi gfx.

 Take Color.......:
                   Colour for the byte deduction comment.
 
 Give Color.......:
                   Colour for the byte add comment.

 Free Color.......:
                   Colour for the freedownload comment.

 Comm Color.......:
                   Colour for a normal comment, where neither bytes were
                   deducted nor added.

 Fake Color.......:
                   Colour of the dCN!FAKE comment.
@endnode

@node "CFGCSC" "ConfSpy Config"

                          @{b}@{u}ConfSpy Config@{ub}@{uu}

       This option is being developed and not yet available!
@endnode

@node "CFGNKL" "NukeLog Config"

                          @{b}@{u}NukeLog Config@{ub}@{uu}

 @{fg shine}Log Day's to keep Uploads:@{fg text}

 This describes how many days the NukeLog entries should be kept. This logfile
 is produced by dCN!NukeLog for every conference on every upload.
 This enables us to find the uploader very fast.
@endnode

